# LifetimeSystem  (sbx)

## Purpose
Generic time-to-live system. Each frame it subtracts the frame delta from every
LifetimeComponent's remaining seconds and deferred-destroys any entity whose remaining time has
reached zero. Used to expire the temporary quads spawned by QuadSpawnSystem; demonstrates
deferred entity destruction.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| LifetimeComponent | write | Remaining time decremented in place; entity destroyed when it hits zero |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| LifetimeComponent | write | m_Remaining decremented by the frame delta |

Entities whose remaining time reaches zero are destroyed via deferred entity destruction (no
component-access declaration required).
